The paper deals with matrix completion problems, which are relevant in several areas of computer science, including recommender systems, machine learning, sensing, computer vision, data science, and predictive analytics. Therefore, the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a likely category because the paper studies the parameterized complexity of the matrix completion problem with respect to several parameters of interest. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category because the paper mentions that matrix completion is a fundamental problem in machine learning. 

cs.IT (Information Theory) is another possible category because the paper deals with the problem of minimizing the number of distinct rows in a completed matrix, which is related to coding theory and compression. 

cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible category because the paper deals with algorithms for completing matrices with missing entries. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible category because the paper mentions that matrix completion is relevant in computer vision.
